Parliament, Wednesday, 09 May 2018 – The Joint Constitutional Review Committee will meet tomorrow to adopt its programme of public hearings on the proposed review of section 25 of the Constitution. Details are as follows: 
	Date: Thursday, 10 May 2018
	Time:  13:00
	Venue: Committee Room V227, Second Floor, Old Assembly Chamber ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE JOINT CONSTITUTIONAL REVIEW COMMITTEE For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)Tel: 021 403 8437Cell: 081 703 9542E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za Democracy is not an event that occurred in 1994. It is a process to which all of us can contribute by making our voices heard in Parliament, in the provincial legislatures and in broader society.Read more